    <div slot="article">
        <p>In today's digital landscape, understanding which Content Management System (CMS) powers a website can provide valuable insights for businesses, developers, and marketers. The CRFT Lookup serves as a sophisticated CMS detector, enabling users to discover the underlying technology stack of any website instantly.</p>

        <p>With hundreds of CMS platforms available, from traditional systems like WordPress to modern headless solutions like Contentful, identifying the specific platform a website uses has traditionally required technical expertiseâ€”until now.</p>

        <h2>Why Detecting CMS Platforms Matters</h2>

        <p>Understanding which CMS a website uses is valuable for multiple reasons: It helps developers evaluate technical requirements for similar projects, enables marketers to understand platform limitations and capabilities, and assists businesses in making informed decisions about their own technology choices.</p>

        <p>The CRFT Lookup eliminates guesswork by providing concrete data about the CMS and related technologies powering any website.</p>

        <h2>How The CRFT Lookup Detects CMS Platforms</h2>

        <p>The CRFT Lookup employs advanced technology scanning capabilities to identify CMS platforms and related technologies. It analyzes a site's code, meta information, and technical signatures that different CMS platforms leave in their implementations.</p>

        <p>When you enter a URL into the CRFT Lookup, it performs a comprehensive scan that can detect popular platforms like WordPress, Drupal, Webflow, and hundreds of others. The tool categorizes these findings and presents them in an easy-to-understand format.</p>

        <h2>Practical Applications of CMS Detection</h2>

        <p>CMS detection capabilities open numerous strategic opportunities: Developers can understand technology stacks for inspiration, businesses can evaluate potential migration paths, and marketers can better understand platform limitations and capabilities.</p>

        <p>Additionally, agencies can better scope projects by understanding client technology requirements, while researchers can analyze CMS market share and trends in specific industries.</p>

        <h2>Beyond Basic CMS Detection</h2>

        <p>The CRFT Lookup doesn't just identify CMS platformsâ€”it provides context about their capabilities, typical use cases, and technical requirements. For each detected platform, users can access information about its features, limitations, and ecosystem.</p>

        <p>This contextual information transforms raw detection data into actionable intelligence, helping users make informed decisions about their own CMS choices.</p>

        <h2>Privacy and Ethical Considerations</h2>

        <p>The CRFT Lookup only detects information that is publicly visible in a website's code. It doesn't access private areas or reveal sensitive configurations.</p>

        <p>The tool is designed for legitimate technical research and educational purposes, providing transparency into the publicly visible aspects of websites' technical infrastructure.</p>

        <p>For developers, marketers, and business professionals looking to gain deeper insights into website technology stacks, the CRFT Lookup's CMS detection capabilities provide a valuable window into the platforms driving digital experiences.</p>
